# Somewhat Mending

<img src="https://cdn.modrinth.com/data/cached_images/b76f5a88d23998a14d5cb83715a0d6924bd5ff0c.png" pixelated alt="Anvil with an enchantment book on top, the project icon" title="Anvil with an enchantment book on top, the project icon" width="175" style="float:right" />

Somewhat Mending brings balance to the Mending enchantment by disabling
the XP pickup repair mechanic and making items with Mending cheaper to repair
with an anvil.

Pairs well with [Anvil Never Too Expensive](https://modrinth.com/mod/ante).

See also: [Unmending](https://modrinth.com/mod/unmending) (Fabric),
          [Mended Mending](https://modrinth.com/mod/mended-mending) (Forge)

## Configuration

```jsonc
{
  // Experience pickup does not repair equipment
  "blockXpRepair": false,
  // Mending affects repairing with an Anvil
  "doAnvilRepairBuff": true,
  // Anvil buff mode
  // Values:
  // - LOG2 (default): Use base 2 logarithmic scale
  // - DEFAULT; Use item base repair cost
  // - MULTIPLY: Multiply repair cost by value
  // - SUBTRACT: Subtract value from repair cost
  // - CONSTANT: Use value as repair cost
  "mode": "LOG2",
  // Value for MULTIPLY mode
  "mulValue": 0.0,
  // Value for SUBTRACT mode
  "subValue": 0,
  // Value for CONSTANT mode
  "constValue": 0
}
